.. but, as I see questions pop up the past few days, I wanted to quickly illustrate why the team -now that insurances got thrown into the mix- is making the pirate booty a lot smaller than originally anticipated:

========

@13omb3r  on the topic of insurance...

I would suggest we first need to agree on high level mechanics that are important to a healthy economy, before considering scenarios and outcomes for individual players and various playstyles.

The most fundamental aspect to model out and agree on is whether we want insurance to be inflationary to the economy or not. For example, if we were to say insurance should be neutral to the economy in terms of ATLAS value then a ship destruction would need to be a transfer of ATLAS value from the hands of the player destroyed to outer space for salvaging and collection. Now if still under this assumption you introduce insurance, your value IN is Ship and contents + Insurance premium. Then the insurance policy purchased by the player would dictate how much of the ATLAS value he gets back in case of destruction and how much is released into outer space for collection.

